list.abstract: fall，英[fɔːl]，美[fɔːl]。英文单词，作动词时，指落下、掉落。作名词时，指跌落、坍塌。短语搭配“fall behind（拖后）”。例句“If you have a pool at home, put a fence around it in case children fall in.（如果你家里有一个游泳池，放一个栅栏围着它以防孩子掉进去）”。 不及动物词性近义词为become、come、lower，名词性近义词为reduction、decline、autumn，动词性近义词为floor、cut sth down，形容词性近义词为autumn。反义词为ascent、rise、ascend。过去式为fell，过去分词为fallen。
《FALL》是中国内地男歌手易烊千玺的第二支个人单曲，由Jon Asher、Ryan Tutton、Dylan Bernard作词、作曲，于2019年8月9日发行。 该单曲采用POP作为大框架，融入Reggae、Urban、Hip-Hop等多种音乐色彩，跳脱常规做加法的动感渲染方式，充分发挥中低音区魅力，歌词以中英文双语带来不一样听感。

yingyinNormal.en: I have 350 cases a day to process. That's a case every 90 seconds. And if I fall behind, I hear from the chief justice.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我每天有350件案子要处理，也就是说每件大概花90秒，如果落下进度会挨首席法官的骂。

yingyinNormal.en: We were kings, Mathews. Kingdoms fall.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们曾经是王，马修斯。王国也会衰落。

yingyinNormal.en: Is that understood? Excellent. Fall out.
yingyinNormal.zh: 明白了吗？很好，解散。

yingyinNormal.en: Whoops. That would've been a nasty fall.
yingyinNormal.zh: 差点就掉下去了。

yingyinNormal.en: The apple doesn't fall far from the tree.
yingyinNormal.zh: 树上掉下的苹果，能落到多远。

yingyinNormal.en: How could you be so stupid to fall in love?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你怎么会这么傻动了真情？

yingyinNormal.en: And, Anna, Arendelle did not fall. It didn't?
yingyinNormal.zh: 还有安娜，艾伦戴尔没有淹没。没有吗？

yingyinNormal.en: No matter what I did, I couldn't fall asleep.
yingyinNormal.zh: 无论我怎么试，就是睡不着。

yingyinNormal.en: When we first spoke, you mentioned early fall.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们第一次谈时，你说初秋。

yingyinNormal.en: Jarvis, anytime now. You will all fall before me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 贾维斯，还等什么。你们都会跪在我面前。

yingyinNormal.en: You're spaghettified as you fall in and you're destroyed.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在你掉入时你就被拉意面了，你就被摧毁了。

yingyinNormal.en: Sorry, no, no, because we were family. Families fall out.
yingyinNormal.zh: 抱歉，不不，我们就像家人。家人也会闹翻。

yingyinNormal.en: They fall away like dominoes. I'm colonizing my own brain.
yingyinNormal.zh: 宛如骨牌效应，我正在征服我的大脑。

yingyinNormal.en: Master the bloomer, and everything else will fall into place.
yingyinNormal.zh: 掌握了这种面包的做法，那么其他的就不在话下。

yingyinNormal.en: What is the matter with you? Do you want to fall into the trap? Do you want to fall into the trap? You did not drop any socks.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你哪根筋不对？你又想跳回去自找苦吃？你根本没掉袜子。

yingyinNormal.en: You know, and then I was, like, "If I fall asleep now, I'll get six hours' sleep. But if I fall asleep now, I'll get five hours' sleep."
yingyinNormal.zh: 你知道的，我会想如果现在睡着，我顶多睡六小时，但是如果我现在睡着，我顶多睡五个小时。

yingyinNormal.en: Riley, how did you fall off the bus? Who does that? Nobody.
yingyinNormal.zh: 莱丽，你怎么会从巴士上摔下来呢？谁会从车上摔下来啊？没人会。

yingyinNormal.en: Because friends like Farkle don't just fall out of thin air.
yingyinNormal.zh: 因为像法尔科这样的朋友是不会凭空掉下来的。

yingyinNormal.en: It is fortunate, then, that they fall to my lot instead of yours.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这么说，这些信总算幸亏碰到了我没有碰到你。

yingyinNormal.en: No. Because I know how to write men that women fall in love with.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不，因为我知道该如何描写让女人陷入爱河的男人。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: become lower in size, amount, or strength
sense_info_list.zh: 下降; 减少; 降低

examination_example.sentence: Worse, the numbers are now <highlight>falling</highlight> at an accelerating rate.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 更糟糕的是，这些数字正在加速下降。

examination_example.sentence: Employment in manufacturing has <highlight>fallen</highlight> from 17 million in 1970 to 12 million in 2015.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 制造业就业人数从1970年的1700万下降到2015年的1200万。

examination_example.sentence: Income inequality usually <highlight>falls</highlight> during a recession, but it has not shrunk in this one.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 收入不平等通常在经济衰退期间下降，但在这次经济衰退中并没有减少。

sense_info_list.zh: 倒下; 落下; 摔倒

examination_example.sentence: Olduvai Gorge, an early hominid site in Tanzania, was found by a butterfly hunter who literally <highlight>fell</highlight> into its deep valley in 1911.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 奥杜瓦伊峡谷是坦桑尼亚早期的原始人遗址，是由一位捕捉蝴蝶的人在1911年掉入峡谷深处时发现的。

sense_info_list.en: change to a particular condition from a different one
sense_info_list.zh: 进入; 变成(某种状态)

examination_example.sentence: But in Osborneland, your first instinct is to <highlight>fall</highlight> into dependency.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是在奥斯本看来，你（失业者）的第一本能反应是陷入（对国家的）依赖。

examination_example.sentence: Suddenly, Britain looks to have <highlight>fallen</highlight> out with its favorite historical form.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 突然间，英国似乎与它最喜欢的历史形态发生了冲突。

examination_example.sentence: There's always a constant fear of <highlight>falling</highlight> behind everyone else on the socially perpetuated "race to the finish line".
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在社会上一直延续的 "冲向终点 "的过程中，人们总有着会落后于人的担忧。

examination_example.sentence: It <highlight>fell</highlight> short of the latter's expectations.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这没有达到后者的预期。

examination_example.sentence: If everyone you know is going to college in the <highlight>fall</highlight>, it seems silly to stay back a year.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果你认识的每个人都要在秋天上大学，那么再推迟一年似乎很傻。

sense_info_list.en: belong to a particular group, subject, or area

examination_example.sentence: Professors portray conservative or classical liberal ideas as <highlight>falling</highlight> outside the boundaries of routine, and sometimes legitimate, intellectual investigation.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 教授们把保守的或典型的自由主义描述为在常规的知识探究范畴之外的东西，有时甚至认为是在正当的知识探究范畴外的东西。

sense_info_list.zh: 突然来到; 突然出现

examination_example.sentence: To prevent teenagers from <highlight>falling</highlight> into blind idolatry, efforts should be made in more ways than one.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 为了防止青少年盲目崇拜偶像，应该从多方面努力。

examination_example.sentence: And researchers are yet to answer the ultimate question of ageing: why does the body ultimately <highlight>fall</highlight> to pieces?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 而且研究人员还没有回答衰老的终极问题:为什么身体最终会崩溃？

examination_example.sentence: If the livestock <highlight>falls</highlight> ill or requires assistance, it can be a long time for farmers to discover.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果牲畜生病或需要帮助，农民可能需要很长时间才能发现。

examination_example.sentence: They rise and <highlight>fall</highlight> from year to year.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它们每年都有升有降。

examination_example.sentence: In China and South Africa traffic deaths have been <highlight>falling</highlight> since 2000, and the Philippines reached its peak four years ago.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 自2000年以来，中国和南非的交通死亡人数一直在下降，而菲律宾在四年前达到了顶峰。

examination_example.sentence: In Estonia and Ireland, for example, the number of death has <highlight>fallen</highlight> by about two thirds since the late 1990s.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 例如，自20世纪90年代末以来，爱沙尼亚和爱尔兰的死亡人数下降了约三分之二。

examination_example.sentence: Even more impressive is the progress in just a single year; human interventions <highlight>fell</highlight> from 0.8 times per thousand miles to 0.2, a 400% improvement.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 无人驾驶技术在短短一年内所取得的进步更是令人震惊: 人工干预次数从每一千公里的0.8次下降到0.2次，提高了400%。

examination_example.sentence: He slipped on ice and <highlight>fell</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他在冰上滑倒了。

examination_example.sentence: A heap of blackened oak beams lay piled up where they had <highlight>fallen</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一堆黑漆漆的橡木梁堆放在它们倒下的地方。

examination_example.sentence: Any one of those mistakes could make it <highlight>fall</highlight> into the uncanny valley.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 其中任何一种错误都可能让它掉进恐怖谷。

examination_example.sentence: They can make viewers feel uneasy because they <highlight>fall</highlight> somewhere between obviously non-human and fully human.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它们会让观众感到不安，因为他们介于明显的非人类和人类之间。

word_usage.usage: fall作“变为…”“进入…状态”时为系动词，后面通常跟形容词，如fall ill 生病。

fall down...表示“跌下...”，fall off/from...表示“从...跌落”，其中down/off/from均为介词，其后直接加宾语，如：
fall down the stairs 跌下楼梯
fall off the bike=fall from the bike 从自行车上跌落
fall作“秋天”时，其前一般要加定冠词the。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 通常指沿斜线或斜坡下降。
指物体从一定高度落下。
fall 与 drop 同义, 指突然或猛烈地降落, 但 fall 也可指任何下落, 同高度或形式无关。
是比较正式的书面用语, 是英式英语表达。"秋季 秋天"名词是它的唯一属性
当它表达为"秋季 秋天"的时候, 是一种口语化用词, 是地道的美式英语的表达。它的主要词性是动词, 主要意思有"落下 倒下, 下垂 低垂, 减少 下降"等等

examination_example.sentence: They <highlight>fell</highlight> victim to eagles.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们成了老鹰的牺牲品。

examination_example.sentence: Starting last Saturday, chains big enough to <highlight>fall</highlight> under the rule will face penalties of up to 2, 000 dollars.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 从上周六开始，受该规定限制的大型连锁餐厅将面临最高2000美元的罚款。

examination_example.sentence: Employed young men are much less likely to live at home than young men without a job, and employment among young men has <highlight>fallen</highlight> significantly in recent decades.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 与没有工作的年轻男性相比，有工作的年轻男性住在家里的可能性要小得多，近几十年来，年轻男性的就业率大幅下降。

examination_example.sentence: Similarly with earnings, young men's wages (after adjusting for inflation) have been on a downward trajectory (轨迹) since 1970 and <highlight>fell</highlight> significantly form 2000 to 2010.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 薪资的情形与此类似，年轻人的工资(经通胀调整后)自1970年以来一直在走下坡路，并在2000至2010年间下降显著。

examination_example.sentence: While cohabitation (同居) has been on the rise, the overall share of young adults either married or living with an unmarried partner has substantially <highlight>fallen</highlight> since 1990.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 虽然同居现象一直在增加，但自1990年以来，已婚或与未婚伴侣同居的年轻人的总体比例大幅下降。

examination_example.sentence: This has resulted in houses <highlight>falling</highlight> into the water.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这导致房屋落入水中。

examination_example.sentence: Losing your balance and <highlight>falling</highlight> isn't pleasant.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 失去平衡并跌倒是不愉快的。

examination_example.sentence: Rather than <highlight>falling</highlight> or failing, you may have good days or better days or not-so-good days

examination_example.sentence: After Hurricane Florence and Hurricane Michael last <highlight>fall</highlight>, USPS worked with state and local election boards to make sure that absentee ballots were available and received on time.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 去年秋天的佛罗伦萨飓风和迈克尔飓风过后，美国邮政总局与各州和地方选举委员会合作，以确保缺席投票能够及时收到。

examination_example.sentence: On a recent <highlight>fall</highlight> morning, a large crowd blocked the steps at one of Venice's main tourist sites, the Rialto Bridge.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 最近一个秋天的早晨，一大群人堵在了威尼斯主要旅游景点——里亚托桥(Rialto Bridge)的台阶处。

examination_example.sentence: In <highlight>fall</highlight> 2010, she helped launch a pilot project in Chicago to see if the iPad could improve working conditions and patient care.

word_usage.usage:
fall down...表示“跌下...”，fall off/from...表示“从...跌落”，其中down/off/from均为介词，其后直接加宾语，如：
fall down the stairs 跌下楼梯
fall off the bike=fall from the bike 从自行车上跌落
fall作“变为…”“进入…状态”时为系动词，后面通常跟形容词，如fall ill 生病。
fall作“秋天”时，其前一般要加定冠词the。

fall 与 drop 同义，指突然或猛烈地降落，但 fall 也可指任何下落，同高度或形式无关。

examination_example.sentence: The curtains were <highlight>falling</highlight> down, the lamps were <highlight>falling</highlight> down, It was a real mess.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 窗帘掉下来了，灯也掉下来了，真是一团糟。

examination_example.sentence: The woman's eye <highlight>fell</highlight> on the man's face, and she immediately looked down and adjusted her scarf.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 女人的目光落在男人的脸上，她立刻低下头，整理了一下围巾。

examination_example.sentence: Also, don't wear loose clothes, long scarves, big necklaces, or loose belts — they get caught in something or <highlight>fall</highlight> into liquid.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 此外，不要穿宽松的衣服、戴长围巾、大项链或宽松的腰带——它们会被什么东西缠住或掉进液体里。

examination_example.sentence: It will <highlight>fall</highlight> out of use some day.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它总有一天会被淘汰的。

examination_example.sentence: It prevents people who are cut off from society <highlight>falling</highlight> victim to cheaters.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它防止与社会隔绝的人成为骗子的牺牲品。

examination_example.sentence: So even if your own efforts at humor <highlight>fall</highlight> short, you might be freeing the long kept humor in others.

examination_example.sentence: He dropped objects of varying weights from the Leaning Tower at Pisa and timed their <highlight>fall</highlight> to the ground.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他从比萨斜塔上扔下不同重量的物体，并记录它们落地的时间。

examination_example.sentence: The curves (曲线) of the buildings perfectly match the rise and <highlight>fall</highlight> of hills, forming a unique view.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 建筑的曲线与山丘的起伏完美地吻合，形成了独特的景观。

examination_example.sentence: Giving up driving is one of the key reasons for a <highlight>fall</highlight> in health and well-being among older people.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 放弃驾驶是老年人健康和幸福感下降的主要原因之一。

examination_example.sentence: One <highlight>fall</highlight>, my wife Elli and I had a single goal: to photograph polar bears.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 有一年秋天，我和我的妻子埃利有一个单一的目标：拍摄北极熊。

examination_example.sentence: Who is eligible: Students aged 15-29, returning to school in the <highlight>fall</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 谁有资格：15-29岁的学生，秋季返校。

examination_example.sentence: Or Africa's Victoria <highlight>Falls</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 或者非洲的维多利亚瀑布。
